6. Define the term software design. Explain how this differs 
from software analysis.
	Software design is the model and plan of what and how the program 
should look like.
	It differs from Software Analysis because the design is the next 
step after establishing what the project requirements are.

7. Explain why a software design is necessary for a software project. 
Can you think of a project without this step? What could be the consequences?
	The Design is of a project is important since it help keeping the big
picture in mind when going after the different goals inside of the project.
The only projects that can work without this step are small programs with little
to no complexity in it's (non) design.

